{"author":{"id":"4bb6c1767e50694cfde61856db22bf137d1651e8a0b5ca858c486db3dd02f280"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1778696217,"nonce":"C3bX5cMk6EGjffe4L9kUl//AzP4=","message":"**Vel-within-RMSE and RMSE-ratio values corrected after go-cue alignment fix (`06f7faf`).**\n\nTrial averaging in absolute trial time before the pairwise-RMSE step inflated both within-cell and across-cell pairwise RMSE because `centerout`'s target-on duration is randomised per trial (~150 ms smear). The fix re-locks each trial to its own go cue before the trial-axis collapse.\n\nHold drift, peak vel, TTP, and CV(peak vel) are scalar per-trial metrics and are unchanged.\n\n| Cell | Pre-fix vel-within-RMSE | Post-fix vel-within-RMSE | Pre-fix vel-RMSE-ratio | Post-fix vel-RMSE-ratio |\n|---|---:|---:|---:|---:|\n| lit__flat_jerk | 0.1086 | 0.1345 | 1.157 | 1.135 |\n| lit__post_jerk | 0.0423 | 0.0436 | 1.229 | 1.229 |\n| lit__full_jerk | 0.0426 | 0.0441 | 1.239 | 1.241 |\n| lit__flat_nojerk | 0.0918 | 0.1166 | 0.978 | 0.984 |\n| **lit__post_nojerk** | **0.0361** | **0.0383** | 1.091 | 1.113 |\n| lit__full_nojerk | 0.0414 | 0.0428 | 1.250 | 1.241 |\n\n**Conclusion unchanged.** The cell ordering on the *operative* metric (absolute within-cell vel-RMSE) is preserved: powerlaw + jerk-off wins, with `lit__post_nojerk` strongest. The framing note (ratio is misleading for this training-method matrix, absolute within-cell RMSE is operative) is unchanged. Every cell is still above the 0.5 RMSE-ratio threshold (consistent with the framing note's read of why that threshold is the wrong test).\n\nFixed by commits `53362d9` / `0e14755` / `c7a7883` / `35769d1` on `feature/go-cue-alignment-fix`.","files":null}]}